def pivot_table(
    data,
    values=None,
    index=None,
    columns=None,
    aggfunc="mean",
    fill_value=None,
    margins=False,
    dropna=True,
    margins_name="All",
    observed=False,
) -> "DataFrame":
    # Convert indices and columns to new form
    index = _convert_by(index)
    columns = _convert_by(columns)
    
    # If aggfunc is a list, handle it differently
    if isinstance(aggfunc, list):
        # Initialize an empty list for pieces and keys
        pieces: List[DataFrame] = []
        keys = []
        
        for func in aggfunc:
            # For each function in aggfunc, call pivot_table recursively and append the result to pieces
            table = data.pivot_table(
                values=values,
                index=index,
                columns=columns,
                fill_value=fill_value,
                aggfunc=func,
                margins=margins,
                dropna=dropna,
                margins_name=margins_name,
                observed=observed,
            )
            
            pieces.append(table)
            keys.append(getattr(func, "__name__", func))

        # Concatenate the pieces and set keys as the columns
        return concat(pieces, keys=keys, axis=1)
